      <byline class="print_byline">By HOWARD G. GOLDBERG</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Goldberg, Howard G</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Howard Goldberg reviews 2005 zinfandel from St Amand Winery (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Few zinfandels are as deeply seductive as the 2005 Mohr-Fry Ranches version from the small St. Amant Winery in Lodi, Calif. Vines planted in 1944 gave the grapes rich character.</p>
        <p>This meaty red tastes of macerated berries, chocolate and oak. The longer it aerates in a glass the spicier it becomes. Pour it with barbecued ribs, beef stew, rack of lamb, shepherd's pie and sausage.</p>
      </block>
